description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have the passion, enthusiasm and knowledge to provide excellent care to acute surgical patients?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you do then the Surgical Directorate is currently looking for Staff Nurses for an exciting newly formed Enhanced Surgical Care Unit with acuity bays which provide an enhanced level of nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver high quality care to patients with complex needs and multiple co-morbidities, we are a forward thinking directorate, who always puts patients first. We strive towards improving our services to meet the ever changing needs of our patients, the workforce and the systems of the future. We need nurses that are passionate about the contribution they make to safe and compassionate patient care, their working environment and colleagues...so why not come and join us!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Surgical Directorate has a desire to encourage and support staff to be the best they can be, so we offer excellent staff development, opportunity for career progression, brilliant team working environments, social events, opportunity to be part of Quality Improvement initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift Patterns are as follows: Long Days (7am-7.30pm) and Nights 7pm-7.30am). The roles do entail internal rotation to nights and also weekends/Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please be aware you will need to be fully flexible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It is essential that you hold current NMC Registration and Surgical experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrea Dearsley andrea.dearsley@rbch.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
